  "datePublished": "2026-03-05",
  "description": "A poem is an artifact that results from writing in which the material qualities of language — sound, rhythm, line break, spacing, image — are compositional elements alongside (or instead of) propositional content. Where an essay is organized by argument and a narrative by plot, a poem is organized by the line.\nThe term verse (from Latin versus, a turning of the plow, hence a line) is sometimes used as a synonym for poetry and sometimes more narrowly for metrically regular poetry, in contrast to free verse or prose poetry.\n",
